Colombian Stocks: Ecopetrol, Rubiales, Canacol, Bancolombia

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-08-18T15:06:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/colombian-stocks-ecopetrol-rubiales-canacol-bancolombia.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:32 a.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 2.7 percent to 13,105.44, while the
Colcap Index fell 2.8 percent to 1,579.38.  Oil companies  fell as crude declined the most in more than
a week amid concern that economic growth in the U.S. and China
is slowing.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
fell 2.8 percent, the biggest intraday drop in a month, to 3,610
pesos. Ecopetrol has fallen short of its share sale target,
saying yesterday it had received orders for 80 percent of the
$1.4 billion in stock it is seeking to sell in Colombia’s
largest planned offering in four years.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PREC)  , the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, fell 3.3 percent
to 44,600 pesos.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Calgary-based oil
company with fields in South America, fell 2.7 percent to 1,620
pesos.  Bancolombia SA (BCOLO)  , Colombia’s biggest bank, fell
3.9 percent, the most intraday in two weeks, to 27,000 pesos.
Bancolombia’s American depositary receipts were lowered to
“underweight” from “neutral” at JPMorgan by equity analyst
Saul Martinez. The 12-month target price is $66.00 per share.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
